        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I had a funny occurrence yesterday. I was selling some stuff in The Bazaar yesterday. I had to run to the bank quickly. Some guy sends me a tell saying he has a friend that wants to buy an item I had. Cool. Where can I meet your friend? The guy says, just set yourself up as a trader again. No problem. I go back, and set up. Here is where it gets weird:</P><P>His friend comes, clicks on my wares and sits down. The other guy sends me another tell asking to knock the price of the item down by 50pp. Both these guys were seriously equipped, and we are talking about an item worth several thousand. At that level who the hell gives a shit about 50pp? My initial thought was there was some sort of bug where when a person is looking at your items for sale, and is in the process of camping, and you change the price of one of your items something goes wonky and he gets your sachel or something. So, I turned off my trader mode. The second I did, the guy stood up. I adjusted my price and re-started in trader mode. The other guy mumbled something to me when I turned my trader mode off, but his friend bought the item, and they left. </P><P>It just seemed too weird. Might be something to keep your eyes open for if you like to do the trader thing. </P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P></P><P> </font></td>

